The paper proposes a neural network-based method for traffic forecasting, which involves learning complex topological structures and capturing dynamic changes in traffic data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), social and information networks (cs.SI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
